---
// Draft Terms of Use for the marketing site. Original wording, with structure/ideas adapted
// from common healthcare-SaaS terms. REVIEW WITH LEGAL COUNSEL before public launch.
// Key items for counsel to confirm:
//  (1) Medical framing — decision-support + "no physician-patient relationship" wording vs.
//      a stronger "medical service provider" posture (Ophthalytics self-identifies as the latter);
//  (2) governing-law state (assumed Georgia from ATDC / Atlanta presence);
//  (3) eligibility / U.S.-only scope; (4) add a postal address for notices;
//  (5) confirm these Terms cover the SITE only, with clinical services under separate agreements.
import Layout from '../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use — Ophthalytics"
  description="The terms governing your use of the Ophthalytics website."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-brand-surface-blue">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-16 md:py-20">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-brand-muted">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-primary">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-ink">Terms of Use</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-ink leading-tight">
        Terms of Use
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-sm text-brand-muted">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <section class="bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-16 md:py-20 space-y-10 text-brand-body leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Acceptance of These Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          These Terms of Use ("Terms") are a binding agreement between you and Ophthalytics, Inc.
          ("Ophthalytics," "we," "us," or "our"). Together with our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-brand-primary font-semibold hover:underline">Privacy Notice</a>,
          they govern your access to and use of our marketing website, including ophthalytics.com and
          ophlx.com, and any content and features offered on it (the "Site"). Please read these Terms
          carefully. By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these Terms and our Privacy Notice.
          If you do not agree, do not use the Site.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          <strong>Scope.</strong> These Terms govern the Site only. Our clinical and diagnostic
          products and services (such as Ocula360, Nsight360, 2nd Opinion, and Ophthal360) are
          provided to healthcare providers and organizations under separate written agreements; those
          agreements—not these Terms—govern access to and use of those products and services.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Who We Are</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Ophthalytics provides AI-assisted retinal diagnostic support services. Our current focus is
          AI-based DRSS (diabetic retinopathy severity scale) scoring to support "second opinion"
          review of retinal imaging, and we intend to expand to additional diagnostic capabilities
          over time. Our tools are designed to support—and not to replace—the independent judgment of
          qualified healthcare professionals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Eligibility</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The Site is intended for users who are at least 18 years old. Our products and services are
          intended for healthcare providers, organizations, and other professional users, and are
          currently offered primarily in the United States. By using the Site, you represent that you
          meet these requirements and that any information you provide is accurate, current, and
          complete.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">No Medical Advice; Informational Purposes Only</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Content on the Site—including text, graphics, images, and other materials ("Content")—is
          provided for general informational purposes only. It is not medical advice and is not a
          substitute for professional medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. We do not warrant the
          accuracy, completeness, usefulness, or adequacy of any Content, and the Site is not designed
          for time-sensitive or life-critical communications. Always seek the advice of a qualified
          healthcare provider with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">No Physician-Patient Relationship; Emergencies</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Your use of the Site does not create a physician-patient relationship between you and
          Ophthalytics. <strong>If you or someone else may be experiencing a medical emergency, call
          911 (or your local emergency number) immediately.</strong> Never disregard professional
          medical advice, or delay seeking it, because of something you have read on the Site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Clinical Decision-Support; Professional Responsibility</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Where we provide AI-assisted diagnostic outputs (such as DRSS scoring or second-opinion
          analysis), those outputs are intended to support clinical decision-making by qualified
          healthcare professionals. They are not a diagnosis and are not a substitute for independent
          professional judgment. The treating or reviewing healthcare professional is responsible for
          evaluating our outputs and for all clinical decisions, diagnoses, and treatment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Do Not Submit Protected Health Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Please do not submit protected health information (PHI), patient-identifiable information, or
          other sensitive personal information through the Site's contact forms, newsletter sign-up, or
          email. The Site is not intended or configured to receive PHI, and any such information should
          be exchanged only through the appropriate, separately governed channels.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Healthcare Provider Representations</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you are a healthcare provider, or act on behalf of a healthcare organization, you
          represent and warrant that you hold all licenses, registrations, rights, consents, and
          authorizations necessary to collect, use, and disclose any patient information in connection
          with our products and services, in compliance with the Health Insurance Portability and
          Accountability Act ("HIPAA") and other applicable privacy and security laws.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">You may use the Site only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You agree not to:</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>use the Site in any way that violates any applicable law or regulation;</li>
          <li>impersonate or attempt to impersonate Ophthalytics, an Ophthalytics employee or agent, or any other person or entity;</li>
          <li>transmit advertising or promotional material without our prior written consent, including any "junk mail," "chain letter," or "spam";</li>
          <li>use any robot, spider, scraper, or other automated means to access, monitor, or copy the Site or its content without our prior written consent;</li>
          <li>introduce any viruses, trojan horses, worms, or other material that is malicious or technologically harmful;</li>
          <li>attempt to gain unauthorized access to, interfere with, damage, or disrupt the Site, the servers on which it is hosted, or any connected systems;</li>
          <li>attack the Site through a denial-of-service or distributed denial-of-service attack; or</li>
          <li>otherwise interfere with the proper working of the Site or any other party's use of it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The Site and all Content, features, and functionality—including text, graphics, logos,
          trademarks, and images—are owned by or licensed to Ophthalytics and are protected by
          applicable intellectual property laws. You may not copy, reproduce, modify, distribute, or
          create derivative works from the Site or its Content without our prior written permission.
          "Ophthalytics" and our product names and logos are our trademarks and may not be used without
          our permission.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The Site may contain links to third-party websites or resources. We provide these for
          convenience only and are not responsible for the content, products, policies, or practices of
          any third party. Your use of third-party sites is at your own risk and subject to their
          terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Reliance on Information Posted</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          The information on the Site is provided for general purposes and may change without notice.
          Any reliance you place on it is strictly at your own risk, and we disclaim all liability
          arising from such reliance by you or anyone you may inform of its contents.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          THE SITE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, WHETHER
          EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR
          PURPOSE, TITLE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted,
          secure, error-free, or free of harmful components.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, OPHTHALYTICS AND ITS OFFICERS, EMPLOYEES, AND AGENTS
          WILL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, SPECIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES,
          OR FOR ANY LOSS OF DATA, PROFITS, OR GOODWILL, ARISING FROM OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OF, OR
          INABILITY TO USE, THE SITE.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Indemnification</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          You agree to indemnify and hold harmless Ophthalytics and its officers, employees, and agents
          from any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses (including reasonable attorneys'
          fees) arising out of your use of the Site or your violation of these Terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may revise these Terms from time to time. Changes are effective when posted, and the "Last
          updated" date above reflects the latest revision. Your continued use of the Site after changes
          take effect constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Governing Law</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Georgia, USA, without regard to its
          conflict-of-laws principles.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Miscellaneous</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions will
          remain in full effect. Our failure to enforce any provision is not a waiver of it. These
          Terms, together with our Privacy Notice, constitute the entire agreement between you and
          Ophthalytics regarding the Site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-ink">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Questions about these Terms? Email us at
          <a href="mailto:info@ophthalytics.com" class="text-brand-primary font-semibold hover:underline">info@ophthalytics.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
